qas.question: In what year did the Norman Conquest take place?
What was the capital of England during the time of the Norman Conquest?
Southampton was important to transit between Winchester and what other region in England in the 11th century?
In what century was Southampton Castle built?
During the 13th century, what did Southampton get in trade for English cloth and wool?

context: Following the Norman Conquest in <a0_0>1066<a0_0/>, Southampton became the major port of transit between the then capital of England, <a1_0>Winchester<a1_0/>, and <a2_0>Normandy<a2_0/>. Southampton Castle was built in the <a3_0>12th<a3_0/> century and by the 13th century Southampton had become a leading port, particularly involved in the import of <a4_0>French wine<a4_0/> in exchange for English cloth and wool.
